rComments: One on the best classes I have taken because of dr. Colvin. Super smart, very well organized lectures with interesting content!! If you ever have the chance to take a class with him, do it! Would recommend.

Do NOT listen to anyone saying this prof is average. He is always engaged, cares about his students, and is overall an amazing lecturer. He has experience in clinical psychology, which shows in the way he teaches. His exams are straightforward but going to class is important as he takes specific topics to test on. 10/10 would recommend!

Amazing. Dr Colvin is very knowledgeable about the material, provides lots of interesting and relevant examples of the course material in his lectures. Dr Colvin is super organized and on top of his game. He is super funny, and his exams are very straightforward MC questions. He does like to ask questions about very specific and narrow topics.

Really engaging in his lectures! You can tell he really cares about the material and in being a good professor. He often shows videos and some funny interactive animations that make his classes interesting. His grading criteria is clear and he gave an optional assignment that could substitute for another evaluation (free chance at a grade boost!).
Glad I got to take a class with Dr. Colvin this semester, his lectures are well structured and he is a really nice prof!
Great guy. He is super engaging and one of the greatest professors I have had at UOttawa so far. He is interested in the subject manner, genuinely cares for his students, and wants to see us succeed.
Really great prof, enjoyed having him this semester!

I don't understand how this man single-handedly turned a class that could be fun into something that boring. It shows he does not want to be a prof, and is doing this course for funding. I believe many of the other students liked him, and he is not mean or anything, but if you have other options take them
